{
  "texts": [
    "Development of new therapeutic techniques and EBPs.",
    "To this point, we have discussed how LLMs could be applied to current approaches to psychotherapy using extant evidence.",
    "However, LLMs and other computational methods could greatly enhance the detection and development of new therapeutic skills and EBPs.",
    "Historically, EBPs have traditionally been developed using human-derived insights and then evaluated through years of clinical trial research.",
    "While EBPs are effective, effect sizes for psychotherapy are typically small 50, 51 and significant proportions of patients do not respond 52."
  ]
}